{
  "text": "for various particle numbers in the torus geometry. Note that the torus geometry can accommodate different parallelogram shapes for the unit cell by continuously varying the angle between two lateral vectors L 1 and L 2 , which can deform the unit cell from square to hexagon [CITATION_1] . As one can see, there are somewhat wild fluctuations in the behavior of the overlap across various particle numbers. Despite these fluctuations, it is possible to extract the following overall behaviors of the overlap.",
